ons for success and happiness\n|\nIt's difficult to cope with the infinite variety of the past, and so we apply filters and settle on a few famous names.\n\n- Chuck Klosterman, but what if we are wrong chuck klosterman\n|\nAgainst all odds, a seed rises from darkness and beautifies the universe.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nWhen you face any difficulty, do not panic but pray.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nLife's a battlefield, and we remain loyal to those who fight for us; those who'd die for us.\n\n- Crystal Woods, Write like no one is reading 3\n|\nThe deeper into this chapter in my life I get, the fainter the hum of crucifixion becomes.\n\n- Maggie\n|\nAnd if you do see any pirates, I don't want you to pick up any rough manners from them. Do you understand?\n\n- Alexander McCall Smith, Explosive Adventures\n|\nCharlotte views her younger selves with a certain detachment. They are herself, but other incarnations, innocents going about half-forgotten business.\n\n- Penelope Lively, How It All Began\n|\nWithout hard work, nothing grows but weeds.\n\n- Gordon\n|\nAs inside of every seed is the power to rise from darkness, inside of everyone is the power to rise from adversity.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nWe are little flames poorly sheltered by frail walls against the storm of dissolution and madness, in which we flicker and sometimes almost go out.\n\n- Erich Maria Remarque, All Quiet on the Western Front\n|\nYour heart can be broken, but your soul never bleeds.\n\n- Deborah\n|\nA living faith, a glorious hope.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nAt times it may feel hopeless. That life is unforgiving. Breathe. In the hopelessness of life, we find hope and promise. We find strength.\n\n- Tania Elizabeth, The Tier of Eternal Grace: The Moon Clearing\n|\nIf we as a society work diligently in every other area of life and neglect the family, it would be analogous to straightening deck chairs on the Titanic.' - Dov Brezak\n\n- Dov Brezak,