imes they're not afraid to stand right up to the devil.\n\n- Donal Harding, Leaving Summer\n|\nI am a man ruled by music- I live, die, fight and survive for it.\n\n- Corey\n|\nPerhaps it's impolite to die so flippantly, after all she's done for me.\n\n- Richard Smyth, Wild Ink\n|\nLove grants us the power to forgive, to love when we’re hurt, but it also gives us the courage to let go, and the understanding that to love, we love freely—at our own choice.\n\n- J.C. Reed, The Lover's Game\n|\nLive simply, share your wealth with others.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nUntil I was left with nothing but life and books, I realised these two gracious gifts, where enough for me to exist.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nLeadership is hard to define and good leadership even harder. But if you can get people to follow you to the ends of the earth, you are a great leader.\n\n- Indra\n|\nSuccess is a work in progress, failure is not the end of the road: it is the strength to continue that matters.\n\n- Ane\n|\nOnce you accept your circumstances and decide to take action, you can welcome change. Change is an opportunity to form new habits and become who you are meant to be.\n\n- Farshad Asl, The 'No Excuses' Mindset: A Life of Purpose, Passion, and Clarity\n|\nWe all know pain,’ Nate said. ‘It becomes a part of us… But it doesn't define us.\n\n- Shona Moyce, Immisceo Taken\n|\nWhat is fair in men, passes away, but not so in art\n\n- Leonardo\n|\nHe would get up and go out into a world which seemed very unfamiliar, but with a tantalizing unfamiliarity like the world of boyhood to which an old man returns.\n\n- Robert Penn Warren, All the King's Men\n|\nMy favorite days are the ones where I deal only with my own team, design, marketing, working on the next accessories collection.\n\n- Diane\n|\nTo draw something is to try to capture it FOREVER, if you really love something, you never try to keep it the way it is forever. You have to let it be free to change\n\n- Cassandra Clare, City of Ashes\n|\nIf you can endure anything, you can become anything.\n\n- Michael\n|\nA tree's beauty lies in its branches, but its strength lies in its roots.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThe death of our self-worth begins at its appraisal, for such an action erroneously implies that our worth can be quantified.\n\n- Craig"